author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football roundup | Sullivan lifts Alder to MOAC Red title
text:
Jonathan Alder 28, River Valley 22 
Sean Sullivan rushed for 218 yards on 37 carries and scored two touchdowns to help Jonathan Alder (8-1, 6-0) clinch the Mid-Ohio Athletic Conference Red Division with a win over visiting River Valley (6-3, 4-2). Sullivan, who has 1,040 rushing yards this season, scored on a 5-yard run to give the Pioneers a 28-14 lead with 4:50 remaining. Jax Harville threw a pair of scoring passes to Carson Parcell for River Valley. 

Hartley 48, Lima Central Catholic 13 
Rian Anderson caught two touchdown passes and host Hartley (6-3) routed visiting Lima Central Catholic (4-5) in nonleague action. Quri Hickman led the Hawks with 106 yards rushing on six carries. 

DeSales 28, St. Charles 6 
Austin Andrews had two touchdown runs, and DeSales (8-1, 2-0) clinched the Central Catholic League Silver Division title with win at host St. Charles (3-6, 0-2). Davion Johnson put the Cardinals ahead early with a 9-yard TD run before Andrews scored his first-half TDs sandwiched around a 51-yard scoring pass from Dylan Todd to Ryan Corkrean. 

Licking Heights 41, Granville 7 
Gabe Caldwell completed 18 of 26 passes for 254 yards and two touchdowns, and Licking Heights (8-1, 3-0) remained tied for first place in the LCL Buckeye by defeating visiting Granville (4-5, 0-3). Nate Thacker caught six passes for 106 yards for the Hornets. 

Heath 53, Lakewood 27 
Quarterback Aaron Latiolais totaled 350 yards and accounted for six touchdowns to lead Heath (5-4, 2-2) over visiting Lakewood (1-7, 0-4) in the LCL Cardinal. Latiolais completed 9 of 10 passes for 270 yards and four touchdown passes and added 80 yards rushing with two TD runs. Heath went on a 26-0 run after Lakewood closed to 21-14 in the second quarter. 

Danville 41, Lucas 0 
Ridge Durbin passed for 341 yards and rushed for 141, and Danville (9-0, 2-0) won the showdown between the No. 1 and 2 teams in the Division VII state poll, defeating visiting Lucas (8-1, 1-1) in the Mid-Buckeye Conference.
